verbLexeme: 1. To jump out of a plane using a parachute. English = parachute.
nominalLexeme: 1. A device which enables you to jump from an aircraft and float to the ground. It consists of a large circle of thin cloth attached to your body by strings. English = parachute.
2. The sport or activity of jumping out of planes with a parachute. English = parachuting.
3. A person who jumps out of planes using a parachute. English = parachutist.
